title: Lima City of The Kings Walking Tour Including Catacombs
description: Maximize your limited vacation time in Peru with a small-group highlights tour of Lima’s UNESCO-listed historic center. Your local guide provides lively commentary as you explore Plaza San Martin, traverse Jiron de La Union for impressive architecture, and then visit landmarks like Plaza de Armas, the Cathedral of Lima, and the Presidential Palace. Conclude your journey at Convent and Museum San Francisco and its Catacombs.
all_descriptions: Maximize your limited vacation time in Peru with a small-group highlights tour of Lima’s UNESCO-listed historic center. Your local guide provides lively commentary as you explore Plaza San Martin, traverse Jiron de La Union for impressive architecture, and then visit landmarks like Plaza de Armas, the Cathedral of Lima, and the Presidential Palace. Conclude your journey at Convent and Museum San Francisco and its Catacombs.

ItineraryThis is a typical itinerary for this productStop At:Plaza San Martin, Av. Nicolas de Pierola cdra. 9, Lima 15001 PeruYour local tour guide will take you to visit this very nice square loved by locals because the gardens and nice atmosphere. Your guide will also give you a good introduction to the history of the country its people and local life. You probably will go inside to one of the buildings around.Duration: 30 minutesStop At:Jiron de La Union, Union Street, Lima PeruUnmissable street, you will be sourrounded with very nice architecture, great wooden balconies, impressive rock carvings and monumental churches and religious altars. The local atmosphere, shops, chicken restaurants plus local music will make your day very excited, happy and for sure interesting!Duration: 30 minutesStop At:Iglesia y Convento La Merced, Jr. de la Union, 621, Lima 15001 PeruThe Minor Basilica and Convent of Nuestra Señora de la Merced is a church located in Lima, Peru. It was designed in the Baroque style. The church was built under the supervision of Friar Miguel de Orenes in 1535. The Blessed Virgin Mary of Mercy (the patroness of the Peruvian Armed Forces) is venerated in the Basilica. The Mercedarians (who evangelized the region) helped to develop Lima by building many of the churches preserved today.Duration: 10 minutesStop At:Plaza de Armas (Plaza Mayor), Jr. Junin and Jr. Carabaya, Lima PeruThis is another HIGHLIGHT! on your tour, is not other than amazing! of course it has an influence of Spain in the architecture (because we been a colony before) is more than atractive and lovely, sourronded with the first palaces,mansions palaces and castles builded in southamerica, the main garden of the square is very well done treated too.Duration: 25 minutesStop At:Presidential Palace (Palacio de Gobierno), Plaza de Armas Zocalo, Lima 15001 PeruWe will take you to the front for an good and right explanation to this building which is the most important house in the whole country. Our president lives in here and works too. The change of the guard happend in here suppost to be everyday at midday but believe it change all the time, great place to see from outside but we are not going insideDuration: 5 minutesStop At:Basilica Catedral De Lima, Jiron Carabaya  s/n, Plaza de Armas de Lima, Lima 15001 PeruThe Basilica Cathedral of Lima, otherwise Lima Cathedral, is a Roman Catholic cathedral located in the Plaza Mayor of downtown Lima, Peru. Construction began in 1535 and completed in 1649. It is dedicated to St John, Apostle and Evangelist.Duration: 5 minutesStop At:Museo Convento San Francisco y Catacumbas, Jiron Ancash, Lima 15001 PeruBefore going to be back, we also will go to visit one of the HIGHLIGHTS! of Lima city which is the San Francisco Convent! but not only that we also will take you to visit its inside CATACOMBS which says a lot about the culture and traditions of local sliving in Lima city during the 16th, 17th and 18th centuries colonial time. we think this is one of the attractions who will make your tour and visit Memorable!Duration: 45 minutes

Gran Hotel Bolivar Lima, Jirón de la Unión 958, Lima 15001, PeruYour local tour guide is going to be waiting for you out of Bolivar Hotel if you don´t need the pick up, he will also give you a good introduction to the history of the country its people and local life. You probably will go inside to one of the buildings around.

Basílica and Convent of San Francisco, Lima, XX3F+V59, Jr. Lampa, Lima 15001, PeruThe church and convent are part of the Historic Centre of Lima, which was added to the UNESCO World Heritage List in 1991.

reviews.title: A Must-Do Tour for First-Time Visitors to Lima!
reviews.text: This tour is an absolute must for anyone visiting Lima for the first time. Whenever I travel to a new city, I make it a point to start with an introductory tour like this to get my bearings and understand the layout of the neighborhoods and local communities. This experience fulfilled that purpose perfectly—but what made it stand out was our guide, Felipe.Admittedly, I was initially unsure about Felipe due to his youthful appearance. I wondered how much insight he could offer. I couldn’t have been more mistaken. Felipe was not only incredibly knowledgeable about Lima’s history and cultural landscape, but also highly attentive to our group’s needs. My family and I truly appreciated his depth of knowledge and engaging style.After the tour, we invited Felipe to join us for dinner. He gladly accepted and even recommended several great restaurants in the area. Once we made our choice, he shared the backstory of the restaurant we selected—its origins, the history of its founder, and its evolution over the years. It added such a rich layer to our dining experience.Felipe exceeded all expectations, and while there’s no guarantee every guide will be quite like him, this tour remains an essential experience for anyone looking to understand both the highlights and realities of life in Lima. I highly recommend it!

reviews.text: We ended up having a private tour. Our guide, Phillipe, was fantastic. His English was execellent and he is very knowledgeable. We enjoyed his stories and seeing the city of Lima thorug his proud eyes.

reviews.title: Fun in Historical Lima
reviews.text: Felipe was amazing! Our tour was very personalized! We went at our own pace, stopped for snacks, and learned so much about the Peruvian history! We all had a blast!

reviews.title: Lima grands
reviews.text: Excellent time. Felipe provided so much extra time with us. Very informative and personal experience. I would do it over again. Loved the catacombs and then some churro. Just go and experience

reviews.title: Great tour of history and catacombs
reviews.text: FILEPE WAS VERY KNOWLEDGEABLE. WE ENJOYED OUR TOUR VERY MUCH. HE TOOK THE TIME TO SHOW US SO MUCH AND EVEN JOINED US FOR LUNCH AT THE END. HIGHY RECOMMEND THIS TOUR OF THE CATACOMBS AND CITY.

reviews.title: Peruvian tour
reviews.text: Felipe, hands down, was the best tour guide ever. He truly gave me an awesome personalized and flexible experience.  It felt like I'd known him for decades. He was knowledgeable and passionate about his work. The historical tour, Sprinkled with a food tour, ended with a night at the water fountain park. Ir was a great day!

reviews.title: Best tour in Lima City
reviews.text: Cesar was my guide for the walking tour of the kings and catacombs. He was so knowledgeable and kind. It was a great tour 10/10 totally recommend and ask for Cesar!!

reviews.title: Amazing tour! You should do it  :)
reviews.text: Amazing tour!! Filipe took his time to answer all my questions. I’ve been to many many tours and this has been my best experience by far. :)

reviews.title: Perfect introduction to Lima
reviews.text: Great tour of the city, would thoroughly recommend it. My tour guide Felipe and driver Jorge were fantastic and very informative.
